    <h3>Translation notes</h3>
    <p>Nordstrom uses years in prison as PD payoffs (lower is better), which is the original formulation. Many textbooks flip the sign and use utility (higher is better). The Nash equilibrium analysis is identical either way. Chicken payoffs here follow Nordstrom's convention: +10 for winning, -1 for swerving alone, -100 for mutual crash.</p>


